cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.WEB, cs.PL, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses software engineering principles and constraints for developing AJAX frameworks and applications, which falls under the scope of software engineering. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper emphasizes user interface component development and improving user interactivity, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction. 
3. cs.WEB (Web Technologies) - The paper discusses the emergence of AJAX as a new breed of web application and examines various AJAX frameworks, which falls under the scope of web technologies. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the architectural properties of AJAX frameworks and introduces the Spiar architectural style, which involves developing intermediary delta-communication between client/server components, which is related to programming languages. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the communication between client/server components in AJAX frameworks, which is related to distributed computing.
